    "asOf": "2004-04-02",
    "date": "2004-06-09T14:05:33Z",
    "text": "Home Mortgage Tax Simplification Act of 2004 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow a tax deduction in the current taxable year of points paid for the refinancing of a principal residence to the extent that the resulting indebtedness does not exceed the sum of: (1) the amount of debt refinanced; plus (2) the lesser of $10,000 or the points paid."
